=== cmd 0: [config --help] ===
Manage treb local config

Manage treb local config stored in .treb/config.local.json

The config defines default values for namespace and network that are used when these flags are not
explicitly provided.

When no subcommand is provided, behaves like `treb config show`.

Usage: treb-cli config [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  show    Show the resolved configuration
  set     Set a config value
  remove  Remove a config value
  help    Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --no-color
          Disable colored output (also respected via NO_COLOR env var)

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
